AddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=84.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   How to get invited into groups</span><hr size=1> A lot of mages have experienced difficulties in finding a regular group, or being desired into those balenced groups that go deep in Sebilis, Chardok, Howling stones, etc.  You wonder, why am I not wanted?  Many times it's your reputation, sometimes it's the mage reputation that is bestode on us due to mages before you.<br>
<br>
Mages, althou about the most offensive power a group could want, have pets that have been known to start trains, break mez's and getting groups killed.  People remember a mage with poor pet control skills, a lot of people will blame the whole class for not controling their pet.  Well, it's not always the case.<br>
<br>
Being wanted in a group as a mage has little to do with your damage potential.<br>
<br>
It has little to do with your debuffs or damage shields<br>
<br>
Getting into a group as a mage has to do with pet control.  You can do everything poorly, do nothing at all, but if you control your pet, you will be wanted.  To be a good mage, learn to control your pet.  If we all learn to control out pet, we will all be more desired and sought after.<br>
<br>
If you don't know how, I found a post I made a few months ago on another board, posted under Library in this forum.  Check it out and learn what you can or ask other respected mages on your server how to control that blasted pet.<br>
<br>
In my opinion, the most dificult class to play in a balanced group (with an enchanter) is a mage.  Controling that pet is a full time job.  Good luck. <p><TABLE>
