<br>
I'm lucky - the person who got me into EQ is an RL friend and a chanter.  We each appreciate the other's skills, we each understand the other's limitations.  I would advise young mages to group with chanters early and often <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Eventually you will become known as a mage that keeps &quot;pet accidents&quot; to a minimum.<br>
<br>
Don't waste much time or energy trying to justify your class to others, either.  That energy is better spent developing a solid group that will appreciate what you have to offer.<br>
<br>
Durga<br>
